H_BT9002: No "else" clause after "else if" clauses.
 [Tips] Removing the condition in the last clause may reduce area and cycles.
        example)
        if (x>0) else if (x<=0); 
        -> if (x>0) else ...
	[Source Lines]
	183(computer.cpp):   else if (sum > (255 << 10))
H_BT9003: "reg" variable is used in automatic scheduling mode.
 [Tips] Use "var" or logic type, if possible, which possibly can reduce the number of cycles.
H_BT9012: The cycle has been increased the number of decoders of the register array for array dmem is limited.
 [Tips] Increasing decoders can improve circuit performance.
        example)
        reg(0:8) ary[3]/* Cyber rw_port = RW2 */ "2" means decoder number.
H_BT9013: Large array(dmem) is bound to a register file.
 [Tips] Bind to memory can reduce area while the number of cycles may increase, in stead.
	[Source Lines]
	19(computer.cpp): uint32_t dmem[DMEM_SIZE]
